<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
One of the key characters discussed by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog (1992)</bibRefCitation>
as the basis for the generic circumscription of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a terrestrial (i.e., non-epiphytic) habit. In the generic delimitation of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog 1992</bibRefCitation>
), the habit is described as herbs, subshrubs, shrubs, or rarely scandent shrubs. The terrestrial habit was considered a character by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog (1992)</bibRefCitation>
to differentiate 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from closely related genera that are epiphytes or lianas. Phylogenetic studies by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was paraphyletic with the exclusion of &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, a group of epiphytic subshrubs from the Andes. Thus, many of the features that differentiated &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as an epiphytic habit and four-valved capsules, are autapomorphic. The transfer of two species from &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well-supported, and combinations were made by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
did not make a combination for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Jost" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Jost" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria andina" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it was considered a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria affinis" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of material in the field and in herbaria allowed us to recognize 
<taxonomicName genus="K." lsidName="K. affinis" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="K." lsidName="K. andina" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as different species. Outlined here are characters to differentiate 
<taxonomicName genus="K." lsidName="K. andina" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName genus="K." lsidName="K. affinis" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological differences and general distribution of Kohleria affinis and K. andina." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/6773835BB260881B85C5B2D1963ECC66" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" tableUuid="6773835BB260881B85C5B2D1963ECC66">1</tableCitation>
for a summary of the characters that are discussed below).
</paragraph>
